02/02/2011
WASHINTON, Unites States -- Prospective NATO membership unites Macedonian society, regardless of ethnic, religious and political differences, Macedonian President Gjorge Ivanov told representatives of the Atlantic Council in Washington on Tuesday (February 1st).
He also voiced hope that Skopje will soon receive an invitation to join the pact, and said membership was Macedonia's top priority.
Ivanov is heading a Macedonian delegation that is meeting with members of congress as well as with Deputy Assistant Secretary of State Thomas Countryman.
(MIA, Inpress - 01/02/11)
